    "index_reference": "bela (person)",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>BELA (Person)</h1><ol><li><p>Beor’s son, a king of Edom who ruled before Israel had a king (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen36:31-Gen36:33\">Genesis 36:31</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen36:31-Gen36:33\">–</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen36:31-Gen36:33\">33</a>). Balaam, the pagan prophet from north Syria, also had a father named Beor (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:5\">Numbers 22:5</a>). So, some scholars have confused the Edomite Bela with Balaam.</p></li><li><p>Benjamin’s oldest son (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:21\">Genesis 46:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr8:1\">1&nbsp;Chronicles 8:1</a>), whose descendants were called Belaites (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:38\">Numbers 26:38</a>).</p></li><li><p>Azaz’s son, a descendant of Reuben. He lived in Gilead in Transjordan. His family had so much land that their cattle lived near the Euphrates River (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:8-1Chr5:9\">1&nbsp;Chronicles 5:8</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:8-1Chr5:9\">–</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:8-1Chr5:9\">9</a>). In the reign of Saul, his family defended their land against a Hagrite opposition.</p></li></ol>",
